{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"There are two groups of women"},{"time":3000,"text":"when it comes to screening mammography --"},{"time":5000,"text":"women in whom mammography works very well"},{"time":8000,"text":"and has saved thousands of lives"},{"time":10000,"text":"and women in whom it doesn't work well at all."},{"time":14000,"text":"Do you know which group you're in?"},{"time":17000,"text":"If you don't, you're not alone."},{"time":19000,"text":"Because the breast has become"},{"time":21000,"text":"a very political organ."},{"time":24000,"text":"The truth has become lost"},{"time":26000,"text":"in all the rhetoric"},{"time":28000,"text":"coming from the press, politicians,"},{"time":30000,"text":"radiologists"},{"time":32000,"text":"and medical imaging companies."},{"time":34000,"text":"I will do my best this morning"},{"time":36000,"text":"to tell you what I think is the truth."},{"time":39000,"text":"But first, my disclosures."},{"time":42000,"text":"I am not a breast cancer survivor."},{"time":44000,"text":"I'm not a radiologist."},{"time":46000,"text":"I don't have any patents,"},{"time":48000,"text":"and I've never received any money from a medical imaging company,"},{"time":51000,"text":"and I am not seeking your vote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"What I am"},{"time":58000,"text":"is a doctor of internal medicine"},{"time":60000,"text":"who became passionately interested in this topic"},{"time":62000,"text":"about 10 years ago"},{"time":64000,"text":"when a patient asked me a question."},{"time":68000,"text":"She came to see me"},{"time":70000,"text":"after discovering a breast lump."},{"time":72000,"text":"Her sister had been diagnosed with breast cancer"},{"time":75000,"text":"in her 40s."},{"time":77000,"text":"She and I were both very pregnant at that time,"},{"time":80000,"text":"and my heart just ached for her,"},{"time":82000,"text":"imagining how afraid she must be."},{"time":85000,"text":"Fortunately, her lump proved to be benign."},{"time":88000,"text":"But she asked me a question:"},{"time":90000,"text":"how confident was I"},{"time":92000,"text":"that I would find a tumor early on her mammogram"},{"time":94000,"text":"if she developed one?"},{"time":96000,"text":"So I studied her mammogram,"},{"time":98000,"text":"and I reviewed the radiology literature,"},{"time":100000,"text":"and I was shocked to discover"},{"time":102000,"text":"that, in her case,"},{"time":104000,"text":"our chances of finding a tumor early on the mammogram"},{"time":106000,"text":"were less than the toss of a coin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"You may recall a year ago"},{"time":111000,"text":"when a firestorm erupted"},{"time":113000,"text":"after the United States Preventive Services Task Force"},{"time":117000,"text":"reviewed the world's mammography screening literature"},{"time":120000,"text":"and issued a guideline"},{"time":122000,"text":"recommending against screening mammograms"},{"time":125000,"text":"in women in their 40s."},{"time":127000,"text":"Now everybody rushed to criticize the Task Force,"},{"time":130000,"text":"even though most of them weren't in anyway familiar"},{"time":132000,"text":"with the mammography studies."},{"time":135000,"text":"It took the Senate just 17 days"},{"time":137000,"text":"to ban the use of the guidelines"},{"time":139000,"text":"in determining insurance coverage."},{"time":143000,"text":"Radiologists were outraged"},{"time":145000,"text":"by the guidelines."},{"time":147000,"text":"The pre-eminent mammographer in the United States"},{"time":149000,"text":"issued the following quote"},{"time":151000,"text":"to the Washington Post."},{"time":154000,"text":"The radiologists were, in turn, criticized"},{"time":157000,"text":"for protecting their own financial self-interest."},{"time":160000,"text":"But in my view,"},{"time":162000,"text":"the radiologists are heroes."},{"time":164000,"text":"There's a shortage of radiologists"},{"time":166000,"text":"qualified to read mammograms,"},{"time":168000,"text":"and that's because mammograms are one of the most complex"},{"time":171000,"text":"of all radiology studies to interpret,"},{"time":174000,"text":"and because radiologists"},{"time":176000,"text":"are sued more often"},{"time":178000,"text":"over missed breast cancer"},{"time":180000,"text":"than any other cause."},{"time":182000,"text":"But that very fact is telling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"Where there is this much legal smoke,"},{"time":188000,"text":"there is likely to be some fire."},{"time":191000,"text":"The factor most responsible for that fire"},{"time":194000,"text":"is breast density."},{"time":198000,"text":"Breast density refers to the relative amount of fat --"},{"time":200000,"text":"pictured here in yellow --"},{"time":202000,"text":"versus connective and epithelial tissues --"},{"time":204000,"text":"pictured in pink."},{"time":206000,"text":"And that proportion"},{"time":208000,"text":"is primarily genetically determined."},{"time":210000,"text":"Two-thirds of women in their 40s"},{"time":212000,"text":"have dense breast tissue,"},{"time":214000,"text":"which is why mammography doesn't work as well in them."},{"time":217000,"text":"And although breast density generally declines with age,"},{"time":220000,"text":"up to a third of women"},{"time":222000,"text":"retain dense breast tissue"},{"time":224000,"text":"for years after menopause."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"So how do you know if your breasts are dense?"},{"time":231000,"text":"Well, you need to read the details"},{"time":233000,"text":"of your mammography report."},{"time":235000,"text":"Radiologists classify breast density"},{"time":237000,"text":"into four categories"},{"time":239000,"text":"based on the appearance of the tissue on a mammogram."},{"time":242000,"text":"If the breast is less than 25 percent dense,"},{"time":245000,"text":"that's called fatty-replaced."},{"time":247000,"text":"The next category"},{"time":249000,"text":"is scattered fibroglandular densities,"},{"time":251000,"text":"followed by heterogeneously dense"},{"time":253000,"text":"and extremely dense."},{"time":255000,"text":"And breasts that fall into these two categories"},{"time":257000,"text":"are considered dense."},{"time":259000,"text":"The problem with breast density"},{"time":261000,"text":"is that it's truly the wolf in sheep's clothing."},{"time":264000,"text":"Both tumors and dense breast tissue"},{"time":266000,"text":"appear white on a mammogram,"},{"time":269000,"text":"and the X-ray often can't distinguish between the two."},{"time":272000,"text":"So it's easy to see this tumor"},{"time":274000,"text":"in the upper part of this fatty breast."},{"time":277000,"text":"But imagine how difficult it would be"},{"time":279000,"text":"to find that tumor in this dense breast."},{"time":282000,"text":"That's why mammograms find"},{"time":284000,"text":"over 80 percent of tumors in fatty breasts,"},{"time":287000,"text":"but as few as 40 percent in extremely dense breasts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"Now it's bad enough that breast density"},{"time":292000,"text":"makes it hard to find a cancer,"},{"time":294000,"text":"but it turns out"},{"time":296000,"text":"that it's also a powerful predictor"},{"time":298000,"text":"of your risk for breast cancer."},{"time":300000,"text":"It's a stronger risk factor"},{"time":302000,"text":"than having a mother or a sister with breast cancer."},{"time":305000,"text":"At the time my patient posed this question to me,"},{"time":308000,"text":"breast density was an obscure topic"},{"time":310000,"text":"in the radiology literature,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and very few women having mammograms,"},{"time":314000,"text":"or the physicians ordering them,"},{"time":316000,"text":"knew about this."},{"time":318000,"text":"But what else could I offer her?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"Mammograms have been around since the 1960's,"},{"time":324000,"text":"and it's changed very little."},{"time":326000,"text":"There have been surprisingly few innovations,"},{"time":329000,"text":"until digital mammography was approved"},{"time":331000,"text":"in 2000."},{"time":333000,"text":"Digital mammography is still an X-ray of the breast,"},{"time":336000,"text":"but the images"},{"time":338000,"text":"can be stored and manipulated digitally,"},{"time":340000,"text":"just like we can with a digital camera."},{"time":343000,"text":"The U.S. has invested"},{"time":345000,"text":"four billion dollars"},{"time":347000,"text":"converting to digital mammography equipment,"},{"time":350000,"text":"and what have we gained from that investment?"},{"time":353000,"text":"In a study funded by over 25 million taxpayer dollars,"},{"time":357000,"text":"digital mammography was found"},{"time":359000,"text":"to be no better over all"},{"time":361000,"text":"than traditional mammography,"},{"time":363000,"text":"and in fact, it was worse in older women."},{"time":366000,"text":"But it was better in one group,"},{"time":369000,"text":"and that was women under 50"},{"time":371000,"text":"who were pre-menopausal and had dense breasts,"},{"time":374000,"text":"and in those women,"},{"time":376000,"text":"digital mammography found twice as many cancers,"},{"time":379000,"text":"but it still only found 60 percent."},{"time":382000,"text":"So digital mammography"},{"time":384000,"text":"has been a giant leap forward"},{"time":386000,"text":"for manufacturers"},{"time":388000,"text":"of digital mammography equipment,"},{"time":390000,"text":"but it's been a very small step forward for"},{"time":392000,"text":"womankind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"What about ultrasound?"},{"time":397000,"text":"Ultrasound generates more biopsies"},{"time":399000,"text":"that are unnecessary relative to other technologies,"},{"time":401000,"text":"so it's not widely used."},{"time":404000,"text":"And MRI is exquisitely sensitive for finding tumors,"},{"time":407000,"text":"but it's also very expensive."},{"time":411000,"text":"If we think about disruptive technology,"},{"time":414000,"text":"we see an almost ubiquitous pattern"},{"time":416000,"text":"of the technology getting smaller and less expensive."},{"time":419000,"text":"Think about iPods compared to stereos."},{"time":422000,"text":"But it's the exact opposite in health care."},{"time":425000,"text":"The machines get ever bigger"},{"time":427000,"text":"and ever more expensive."},{"time":431000,"text":"Screening the average young woman with an MRI"},{"time":434000,"text":"is kind of like driving to the grocery store in a Hummer."},{"time":438000,"text":"It's just way too much equipment."},{"time":440000,"text":"One MRI scan"},{"time":442000,"text":"costs 10 times what a digital mammogram costs."},{"time":445000,"text":"And sooner or later, we're going to have to accept the fact"},{"time":447000,"text":"that health care innovation"},{"time":449000,"text":"can't always come at a much higher price."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454000,"text":"Malcolm Gladwell wrote an article in the New Yorker"},{"time":456000,"text":"on innovation,"},{"time":458000,"text":"and he made the case that scientific discoveries"},{"time":461000,"text":"are rarely the product of one individual's genius."},{"time":465000,"text":"Rather, big ideas can be orchestrated,"},{"time":468000,"text":"if you can simply gather"},{"time":470000,"text":"people with different perspectives in a room"},{"time":472000,"text":"and get them to talk about things"},{"time":474000,"text":"that they don't ordinarily talk about."},{"time":476000,"text":"It's like the essence of TED."},{"time":479000,"text":"He quotes one innovator who says,"},{"time":481000,"text":"\"The only time a physician and a physicist get together"},{"time":485000,"text":"is when the physicist gets sick.\""},{"time":487000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":489000,"text":"This makes no sense,"},{"time":491000,"text":"because physicians have all kinds of problems"},{"time":493000,"text":"that they don't realize have solutions."},{"time":496000,"text":"And physicists have all kinds of solutions for things"},{"time":498000,"text":"that they don't realize are problems."},{"time":501000,"text":"Now, take a look at this cartoon"},{"time":504000,"text":"that accompanied Gladwell's article,"},{"time":506000,"text":"and tell me if you see something disturbing"},{"time":508000,"text":"about this depiction of innovative thinkers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513000,"text":"So if you will allow me a little creative license,"},{"time":517000,"text":"I will tell you the story"},{"time":519000,"text":"of the serendipitous collision"},{"time":521000,"text":"of my patient's problem"},{"time":523000,"text":"with a physicist's solution."},{"time":525000,"text":"Shortly after her visit,"},{"time":527000,"text":"I was introduced to a nuclear physicist"},{"time":529000,"text":"at Mayo"},{"time":531000,"text":"named Michael O'Conner,"},{"time":533000,"text":"who was a specialist in cardiac imaging,"},{"time":535000,"text":"something I had nothing to do with."},{"time":537000,"text":"And he happened to tell me"},{"time":539000,"text":"about a conference he'd just returned from in Israel,"},{"time":542000,"text":"where they were talking about a new type of gamma detector."},{"time":545000,"text":"Now gamma imaging has been around for a long time"},{"time":547000,"text":"to image the heart,"},{"time":549000,"text":"and it had even been tried to image the breast."},{"time":552000,"text":"But the problem was"},{"time":554000,"text":"that the gamma detectors"},{"time":556000,"text":"were these huge, bulky tubes,"},{"time":558000,"text":"and they were filled with these scintillating crystals,"},{"time":560000,"text":"and you just couldn't get them close enough around the breast"},{"time":563000,"text":"to find small tumors."},{"time":565000,"text":"But the potential advantage was"},{"time":567000,"text":"that gamma rays, unlike X-rays,"},{"time":569000,"text":"are not influenced by breast density."},{"time":572000,"text":"But this technology"},{"time":574000,"text":"could not find tumors when they're small,"},{"time":576000,"text":"and finding a small tumor is critical for survival."},{"time":579000,"text":"If you can find a tumor"},{"time":581000,"text":"when it's less than a centimeter,"},{"time":583000,"text":"survival exceeds 90 percent,"},{"time":585000,"text":"but drops off rapidly"},{"time":587000,"text":"as tumor size increases."},{"time":590000,"text":"But Michael told me about"},{"time":592000,"text":"a new type of gamma detector that he'd seen,"},{"time":594000,"text":"and this is it."},{"time":596000,"text":"It's made"},{"time":598000,"text":"not of a bulky tube,"},{"time":600000,"text":"but of a thin layer of a semiconductor material"},{"time":603000,"text":"that serves as the gamma detector."},{"time":605000,"text":"And I started talking to him"},{"time":607000,"text":"about this problem with breast density,"},{"time":609000,"text":"and we realized that we might be able to get this detector"},{"time":612000,"text":"close enough around the breast"},{"time":614000,"text":"to actually find small tumors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"So after putting together"},{"time":618000,"text":"a grid of these cubes with tape --"},{"time":621000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":624000,"text":"-- Michael hacked off the X-ray plate"},{"time":627000,"text":"of a mammography machine"},{"time":629000,"text":"that was about to be thrown out,"},{"time":631000,"text":"and we attached the new detector,"},{"time":634000,"text":"and we decided to call this machine"},{"time":636000,"text":"Molecular Breast Imaging, or MBI."},{"time":640000,"text":"This is an image from our first patient."},{"time":642000,"text":"And you can see, using the old gamma technology,"},{"time":644000,"text":"that it just looked like noise."},{"time":646000,"text":"But using our new detector,"},{"time":648000,"text":"we could begin to see the outline of a tumor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651000,"text":"So here we were, a nuclear physicist,"},{"time":653000,"text":"an internist,"},{"time":655000,"text":"soon joined by Carrie Hruska, a biomedical engineer,"},{"time":658000,"text":"and two radiologists,"},{"time":660000,"text":"and we were trying to take on"},{"time":662000,"text":"the entrenched world of mammography"},{"time":664000,"text":"with a machine that was held together by duct tape."},{"time":668000,"text":"To say that we faced"},{"time":670000,"text":"high doses of skepticism"},{"time":672000,"text":"in those early years"},{"time":674000,"text":"is just a huge understatement,"},{"time":676000,"text":"but we were so convinced that we might be able to make this work"},{"time":679000,"text":"that we chipped away with incremental modifications"},{"time":682000,"text":"to this system."},{"time":684000,"text":"This is our current detector."},{"time":686000,"text":"And you can see that it looks a lot different."},{"time":688000,"text":"The duct tape is gone,"},{"time":692000,"text":"and we added a second detector on top of the breast,"},{"time":694000,"text":"which has further improved our tumor detection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"So how does this work?"},{"time":699000,"text":"The patient receives an injection of a radio tracer"},{"time":702000,"text":"that's taken up by rapidly proliferating tumor cells,"},{"time":705000,"text":"but not by normal cells,"},{"time":707000,"text":"and this is the key difference from mammography."},{"time":710000,"text":"Mammography relies on differences"},{"time":712000,"text":"in the appearance of the tumor from the background tissue,"},{"time":715000,"text":"and we've seen that those differences"},{"time":717000,"text":"can be obscured in a dense breast."},{"time":720000,"text":"But MBI exploits"},{"time":722000,"text":"the different molecular behavior of tumors,"},{"time":725000,"text":"and therefore, it's impervious to breast density."},{"time":729000,"text":"After the injection,"},{"time":731000,"text":"the patient's breast is placed between the detectors."},{"time":733000,"text":"And if you've ever had a mammogram --"},{"time":735000,"text":"if you're old enough to have had a mammogram --"},{"time":737000,"text":"you know what comes next:"},{"time":739000,"text":"pain."},{"time":741000,"text":"You may be surprised to know"},{"time":743000,"text":"that mammography is the only radiologic study"},{"time":746000,"text":"that's regulated by federal law,"},{"time":748000,"text":"and the law requires"},{"time":750000,"text":"that the equivalent of a 40-pound car battery"},{"time":753000,"text":"come down on your breast during this study."},{"time":757000,"text":"But with MBI,"},{"time":759000,"text":"we use just light, pain-free compression."},{"time":762000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":768000,"text":"And the detector"},{"time":770000,"text":"then transmits the image to the computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772000,"text":"So here's an example."},{"time":774000,"text":"You can see, on the right, a mammogram"},{"time":776000,"text":"showing a faint tumor,"},{"time":778000,"text":"the edges of which are blurred by the dense tissue."},{"time":780000,"text":"But the MBI image shows that tumor much more clearly,"},{"time":783000,"text":"as well as a second tumor,"},{"time":785000,"text":"which profoundly influence that patient's surgical options."},{"time":789000,"text":"In this example, although the mammogram found one tumor,"},{"time":792000,"text":"we were able to demonstrate three discrete tumors --"},{"time":795000,"text":"one is small as three millimeters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798000,"text":"Our big break came in 2004."},{"time":803000,"text":"After we had demonstrated that we could find small tumors,"},{"time":806000,"text":"we used these images"},{"time":808000,"text":"to submit a grant to the Susan G. Komen Foundation."},{"time":811000,"text":"And we were elated when they took a chance"},{"time":814000,"text":"on a team of completely unknown investigators"},{"time":816000,"text":"and funded us to study"},{"time":818000,"text":"1,000 women with dense breasts,"},{"time":820000,"text":"comparing a screening mammogram to an MBI."},{"time":823000,"text":"Of the tumors that we found,"},{"time":825000,"text":"mammography found"},{"time":827000,"text":"only 25 percent of those tumors."},{"time":830000,"text":"MBI found 83 percent."},{"time":833000,"text":"Here's an example from that screening study."},{"time":836000,"text":"The digital mammogram was read as normal"},{"time":838000,"text":"and shows lots of dense tissue,"},{"time":840000,"text":"but the MBI shows an area of intense uptake,"},{"time":843000,"text":"which correlated with a two-centimeter tumor."},{"time":846000,"text":"In this case, a one-centimeter tumor."},{"time":849000,"text":"And in this case,"},{"time":851000,"text":"a 45-year-old medical secretary at Mayo,"},{"time":854000,"text":"who had lost her mother to breast cancer when she was very young,"},{"time":857000,"text":"wanted to enroll in our study."},{"time":859000,"text":"And her mammogram showed an area of very dense tissue,"},{"time":862000,"text":"but her MBI showed an area"},{"time":864000,"text":"of worrisome uptake,"},{"time":866000,"text":"which we can also see on a color image."},{"time":869000,"text":"And this corresponded"},{"time":871000,"text":"to a tumor the size of a golf ball."},{"time":873000,"text":"But fortunately it was removed"},{"time":875000,"text":"before it had spread to her lymph nodes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"So now that we knew that this technology"},{"time":881000,"text":"could find three times more tumors in a dense breast,"},{"time":884000,"text":"we had to solve one very important problem."},{"time":887000,"text":"We had to figure out how to lower the radiation dose,"},{"time":890000,"text":"and we have spent the last three years"},{"time":893000,"text":"making modifications to every aspect of the imaging system"},{"time":896000,"text":"to allow this."},{"time":898000,"text":"And I'm very happy to report that we're now using a dose of radiation"},{"time":901000,"text":"that is equivalent to the effective dose"},{"time":903000,"text":"from one digital mammogram."},{"time":905000,"text":"And at this low dose, we're continuing this screening study,"},{"time":908000,"text":"and this image from three weeks ago"},{"time":911000,"text":"in a 67-year-old woman"},{"time":913000,"text":"shows a normal digital mammogram,"},{"time":915000,"text":"but an MBI image"},{"time":917000,"text":"showing an uptake that proved to be a large cancer."},{"time":920000,"text":"So this is not just young women that it's benefiting."},{"time":923000,"text":"It's also older women with dense tissue."},{"time":926000,"text":"And we're now routinely using one-fifth the radiation dose"},{"time":929000,"text":"that's used in any other type of gamma technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"MBI generates four images per breast."},{"time":936000,"text":"MRI generates over a thousand."},{"time":939000,"text":"It takes a radiologist"},{"time":941000,"text":"years of specialty training"},{"time":943000,"text":"to become expert in differentiating"},{"time":945000,"text":"the normal anatomic detail"},{"time":947000,"text":"from the worrisome finding."},{"time":949000,"text":"But I suspect even the non-radiologists in the room"},{"time":952000,"text":"can find the tumor on the MBI image."},{"time":955000,"text":"But this is why MBI"},{"time":957000,"text":"is so potentially disruptive --"},{"time":959000,"text":"it's as accurate as MRI,"},{"time":961000,"text":"it's far less complex to interpret,"},{"time":964000,"text":"and it's a fraction of the cost."},{"time":966000,"text":"But you can understand why there may be"},{"time":968000,"text":"forces in the breast-imaging world"},{"time":970000,"text":"who prefer the status quo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":974000,"text":"After achieving what we felt were remarkable results,"},{"time":977000,"text":"our manuscript was rejected"},{"time":980000,"text":"by four journals."},{"time":982000,"text":"After the fourth rejection,"},{"time":984000,"text":"we requested reconsideration of the manuscript,"},{"time":986000,"text":"because we strongly suspected"},{"time":988000,"text":"that one of the reviewers who had rejected it"},{"time":990000,"text":"had a financial conflict of interest"},{"time":992000,"text":"in a competing technology."},{"time":995000,"text":"Our manuscript was then accepted"},{"time":997000,"text":"and will be published later this month"},{"time":1000000,"text":"in the journal Radiology."},{"time":1002000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1010000,"text":"We still need to complete the screening study using the low dose,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and then our findings will need to be replicated"},{"time":1015000,"text":"at other institutions,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"and this could take five or more years."},{"time":1020000,"text":"If this technology is widely adopted,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"I will not benefit financially in any way,"},{"time":1026000,"text":"and that is very important to me,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"because it allows me to continue to tell you the truth."},{"time":1033000,"text":"But I recognize --"},{"time":1035000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1039000,"text":"I recognize that the adoption of this technology"},{"time":1042000,"text":"will depend as much on economic"},{"time":1044000,"text":"and political forces"},{"time":1046000,"text":"as it will on the soundness of the science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049000,"text":"The MBI unit has now been FDA approved,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"but it's not yet widely available."},{"time":1055000,"text":"So until something is available"},{"time":1057000,"text":"for women with dense breasts,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"there are things that you should know"},{"time":1061000,"text":"to protect yourself."},{"time":1063000,"text":"First, know your density."},{"time":1065000,"text":"Ninety percent of women don't,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"and 95 percent of women don't know"},{"time":1069000,"text":"that it increases your breast cancer risk."},{"time":1072000,"text":"The State of Connecticut became the first and only state"},{"time":1075000,"text":"to mandate that women receive notification"},{"time":1077000,"text":"of their breast density"},{"time":1079000,"text":"after a mammogram."},{"time":1082000,"text":"I was at a conference of 60,000 people in breast-imaging"},{"time":1085000,"text":"last week in Chicago,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"and I was stunned that there was a heated debate"},{"time":1090000,"text":"as to whether we should be telling women"},{"time":1092000,"text":"what their breast density is."},{"time":1094000,"text":"Of course we should."},{"time":1096000,"text":"And if you don't know, please ask your doctor"},{"time":1099000,"text":"or read the details of your mammography report."},{"time":1102000,"text":"Second, if you're pre-menopausal,"},{"time":1104000,"text":"try to schedule your mammogram"},{"time":1106000,"text":"in the first two weeks of your menstrual cycle,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"when breast density is relatively lower."},{"time":1111000,"text":"Third, if you notice a persistent change in your breast,"},{"time":1114000,"text":"insist on additional imaging."},{"time":1117000,"text":"And fourth and most important,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"the mammography debate will rage on,"},{"time":1122000,"text":"but I do believe that all women 40 and older"},{"time":1125000,"text":"should have an annual mammogram."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1127000,"text":"Mammography isn't perfect,"},{"time":1129000,"text":"but it's the only test that's been proven"},{"time":1131000,"text":"to reduce mortality from breast cancer."},{"time":1134000,"text":"But this mortality banner"},{"time":1136000,"text":"is the very sword"},{"time":1138000,"text":"which mammography's most ardent advocates use"},{"time":1141000,"text":"to deter innovation."},{"time":1143000,"text":"Some women who develop breast cancer"},{"time":1146000,"text":"die from it many years later,"},{"time":1148000,"text":"and most women, thankfully, survive."},{"time":1150000,"text":"So it takes 10 or more years"},{"time":1152000,"text":"for any screening method"},{"time":1154000,"text":"to demonstrate a reduction"},{"time":1156000,"text":"in mortality from breast cancer."},{"time":1158000,"text":"Mammography's the only one that's been around long enough"},{"time":1160000,"text":"to have a chance of making that claim."},{"time":1163000,"text":"It is time for us to accept"},{"time":1166000,"text":"both the extraordinary successes of mammography"},{"time":1168000,"text":"and the limitations."},{"time":1170000,"text":"We need to individualize screening"},{"time":1172000,"text":"based on density."},{"time":1174000,"text":"For women without dense breasts,"},{"time":1176000,"text":"mammography is the best choice."},{"time":1179000,"text":"But for women with dense breasts;"},{"time":1181000,"text":"we shouldn't abandon screening altogether,"},{"time":1183000,"text":"we need to offer them something better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1188000,"text":"The babies that we were carrying"},{"time":1190000,"text":"when my patient first asked me this question"},{"time":1193000,"text":"are now both in middle school,"},{"time":1196000,"text":"and the answer has been so slow to come."},{"time":1201000,"text":"She's given me her blessing"},{"time":1203000,"text":"to share this story with you."},{"time":1206000,"text":"After undergoing biopsies"},{"time":1208000,"text":"that further increased her risk for cancer"},{"time":1211000,"text":"and losing her sister to cancer,"},{"time":1213000,"text":"she made the difficult decision"},{"time":1215000,"text":"to have a prophylactic mastectomy."},{"time":1219000,"text":"We can and must do better,"},{"time":1222000,"text":"not just in time for her granddaughters"},{"time":1225000,"text":"and my daughters,"},{"time":1227000,"text":"but in time for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1229000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1231000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}